unittitle_ssm: Gay and Lesbian Pulp Fiction Collection
abstract_ssm: Pulp magazines, often known as "pulp fiction," were commonly used to publish and distribute genre fiction in the first half of the 20th century. This collection contains over 1000 volumes of gay and lesbian erotica published in pulp magazines between 1955 and 1988. Many of these novels were published pseudonymously to evade anti-vice Comstock Laws.
